# ADR-005 — Why Certified Semantic Models

**Status:** Accepted

**Date:** 2026-07-01

**Decision Makers:** UK Future Innovations (Atlas Engineering)

---

# Context

Atlas will expose business intelligence through Power BI dashboards, future web applications, APIs and AI services.

Without governance, different developers may create their own DAX measures and KPIs within individual semantic models or reports. Over time this leads to inconsistent business definitions, duplicated logic and conflicting reporting.

For example:

Developer A defines:

Total Profit

Developer B defines:

Net Profit

Developer C defines:

Trading Profit

Although each measure appears similar, slight differences in calculation logic can produce different values across reports, reducing confidence in the platform.

As Atlas grows into a commercial product, consistency of business metrics is essential.

---

# Decision

Atlas will adopt a **Certified Semantic Model** as the single source of truth for all business calculations.

Business measures, KPIs and calculated metrics will be defined once within the certified semantic model and reused by every consuming application.

All Power BI reports, dashboards and future AI services should consume these centrally managed measures rather than creating local report-specific calculations.

