# Benefits

Using a certified semantic model provides:

- Single version of the truth.
- Consistent KPI calculations.
- Shared DAX measures.
- Reduced duplication.
- Easier maintenance.
- Simplified report development.
- Trusted business reporting.
- Improved governance.
- Better scalability as additional products are developed.

---

# Measure Governance

Measures will be organised into logical business areas.

Examples include:

## Price

- Current Price
- Opening Price
- Daily High
- Daily Low
- Moving Average

## Trading

- ABS-1 Signal
- Buy Signals
- Sell Signals
- Hold Signals

## Performance

- Total Trades
- Winning Trades
- Win Percentage
- Profit/Loss
- Maximum Drawdown

## AI (Future)

- Atlas Intelligence Score
- Confidence Score
- Sentiment Rating

This organisation improves discoverability and promotes consistent report development.

---

# Future Certification Process

The Atlas Semantic Model will follow Microsoft's endorsement model.

Development progresses through:

Uncertified

↓

Promoted

↓

Certified

Only certified semantic models should be used for production dashboards and customer-facing reports.

---

# Consequences

Positive

- Consistent reporting across the platform.
- Easier onboarding of future developers.
- Reusable business logic.
- Better performance through reduced duplicated calculations.
- Enterprise-grade governance.

Negative

- Slightly more effort required when introducing new KPIs.
- Changes to business logic require governance and version control.

The advantages significantly outweigh these additional governance requirements.

---

# Future Enhancements

Future versions of Atlas may include:

- Calculation Groups
- Shared KPI catalogue
- Versioned semantic models
- Automated semantic model deployment
- AI-generated documentation for measures
- Semantic model testing within CI/CD pipelines

---

# Summary

Atlas adopts Certified Semantic Models to ensure that every dashboard, report, API and AI component consumes the same centrally governed business definitions.

This decision establishes a single source of truth for business calculations and aligns Atlas with Microsoft Fabric and Power BI enterprise best practices.